legend.near: bottom-right

implementation_notes: |md
  ### Mathematical Equivalence
  Standard MLP: $Y = \text{GeLU}(XW_1 + b_1)W_2 + b_2$
  
  **Parallel Split:**
  1. $W_1 = [W_{1,a}, W_{1,b}]$ (Column Split)
  2. $W_2 = [W_{2,a}; W_{2,b}]$ (Row Split)
  3. $Y = \text{AllReduce}(\text{GeLU}(XW_{1,i})W_{2,i})$
  
  **Complexity:**
  - Memory: $1/TP$ per GPU
  - Compute: $1/TP$ per GPU
  - Communication: Only 1 sync point
|
implementation_notes.near: bottom-left
implementation_notes.width: 350